        "body": "## Problem\n\nThe documentation at https://docs.deno.com currently lacks a copy-to-clipboard button on code blocks. Users must manually select and copy command-line examples, which is inefficient and error-prone, especially for long commands or multiline examples.\n\n## Proposed solution\n\nAdd a visible copy button to each code block (`<pre><code>`) that:\n- appears on the top-right of the code container,\n- copies the raw code to clipboard on click (removes shell prompts like `$`, `>`, `❯`),\n- shows a tick/check icon after copy for user feedback,\n- stays pinned even when the code block is scrollable horizontally.\n\n## Why this matters\n\nThis improves the UX significantly, especially for beginners trying to follow installation and usage commands from the docs. It's also a widely used feature in modern documentation systems (e.g., ChatGPT, GitHub DocsETC).\n\n## Screenshots\n\n**Before:**\n\n<img width=\"1600\" height=\"1005\" alt=\"Before copy button\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d11eb1fa-37dc-41d5-812f-cab7b98bb6ed\" />\n\n**After:**\n\n<img width=\"1600\" height=\"1007\" alt=\"After copy button added\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/310dd140-af60-479a-b265-99f38382c9c0\" />\n\n## Notes\n\nI have implemented a working version in my fork here:  \nhttps://github.com/shekhar-narayan-mishra/docs/tree/feat/docs-copy-button\n\nI will open a PR referencing this issue shortly.\n",
